STATE of North Carolina
v.
Tony Eugene HOWELL. No. 136P06. Supreme Court of North Carolina. May 4, 2006. Tony Eugene Howell, Pro Se. William P. Hart, Senior Deputy Attorney General, Garry W. Frank, District Attorney, for State.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 14th day of March 2006 in this matter for a writ of certiorari to review the order of the North Carolina Court of Appeals, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals:

"Dismissed by order of the Court in conference, this the 4th day of May 2006."
